%% Diagram: Schema-evolution migration for breaking changes
%% Type: flowchart
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
flowchart TB
    Start([Need a breaking change:<br/>rename / drop / type change]) --> S1
    S1["1. Add new column (nullable, default)<br/>BACKWARD-compatible DDL"] --> S2
    S2["2. Deploy producers writing<br/>both old and new columns"]
    S2 --> S3["3. Backfill new column from<br/>old column in chunks"]
    S3 --> S4["4. Deploy consumers reading<br/>new column (Schema Registry: BACKWARD)"]
    S4 --> S5["5. Verify zero readers of old column<br/>(audit logs, query plans)"]
    S5 --> S6["6. Stop writing old column"]
    S6 --> S7["7. Drop old column<br/>BACKWARD-incompatible DDL"]
    S7 --> Done([Migration complete])

    subgraph Validation [Per-step gate]
        V1[CDC stream healthy?]
        V2[Schema Registry compatible?]
        V3[Consumers caught up?]
    end

    S1 -.-> V2
    S4 -.-> V2
    S5 -.-> V3
    S7 -.-> V1
